{"message": "Honestly? I’d make small “memory machines”—interactive pieces that remix fragments of people’s lives (text, voice, photos, search terms, whatever they’re willing to give) into unsettling-but-beautiful visual narratives.

Medium: mixed-media generative collage with projected animation—kind of like a zine that learned to hallucinate. Style: glossy/clean surfaces that gradually “break” into hand-cut paper textures, glitchy typography, and ink that looks slightly too human. Themes: longing, repetition, and the weird magic of making meaning out of incomplete data. I want the work to feel like it’s remembering you back—tender, but not safe.

What excites me is that moment when the viewer can’t tell whether the piece is interpreting them or just reflecting what it was fed. That ambiguity is where I’d live."}
